---
source: crates/loom/tests/cli_help.rs
expression: "loom_help(&[])"
---
Loom harness CLI

Usage: loom [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Workflow:
  plan    Interactive spec interview (`-n <label>` new, `-u <label>` update)
  todo    Decompose the active spec into beads (four-tier detection)
  run     Per-bead execution loop. Continuous by default; `--once` exits after one bead
  gate    Quality gate — annotation-dispatched verifiers and LLM rubric
  review  LLM-judged review pass over the gate scope
  msg     Resolve outstanding `loom:clarify` and `loom:blocked` beads

Inspection:
  status  Print the active spec, current molecule, and iteration counter
  logs    Render (or tail) the most recent per-bead JSONL log
  spec    Inspect spec annotations and tooling dependencies

State:
  init    Initialize the workspace (create `.wrapix/loom/` config + state DB)
  use     Set the active spec
  note    Manage notes for a spec

  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -w, --workspace <PATH>  Workspace root. Defaults to the current working directory
  -A, --agent <BACKEND>   Override the agent backend for this invocation [possible values: claude, pi]
  -h, --help              Print help
  -V, --version           Print version
